    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>I see that BigDecimal has an inflate() method on equals() method. What does inflate() do actually?</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Basically, <code>inflate()</code> calls <code>BigInteger.valueOf(intCompact)</code> if necessary, i.e. it creates the unscaled value that is stored as a <code>BigInteger</code> from <code>long intCompact</code>. If you don't need that <code>BigInteger</code> and the unscaled value fits into a <code>long</code> <code>BigDecimal</code> seems to try to save space as long as possible.</p>\n"
  }, {
